Public transport (MHD) pragonics will introduce the chip into their ticketing system on Wednesday.
Wednesday, October 1, 2008 will be included in the history of Pražský Dopravní podnik (the Pragical Transportation Agency) as the date on which the first passengers will ride the subway, trams and buses, which, instead of having a paper ticket, will have an electronic coupon in their pocket.
At the moment, the latter is accessible for about a hundred thousand people, owners of the Opencard chip card.
Passengers can buy a 30-day coupon or 90-day coupon (this coupon will be valid from 1 January 2009) and at the same time have it recorded on their smart card in the information points and offices of the Dopravní podnik (the Agency of Transportation), located in the metro stations Muzeum, Můstek, Nádraží Holešovice, Anděl, Roztyly, Letňany, Kobylisy, Rajská zahrada, Kačerov and Luka.
From yesterday, there is also the possibility to buy coupons online on the Dopravní podnik web pages: www.dpp.cz.
More than four hundred people took advantage of the service during the morning.
Those who will begin to use the online store can permanently forget the counters in metro stations, where they had until now to tread impatience in long tails in order to obtain paper tickets.
Indeed, they will buy their coupon on the internet and record it on their Opencard card in one of the thirteen Městská knihovna (municipal libraries).
"In these points of contact, there is a desk with trained staff at the passenger's disposal, which will help those interested with the internet purchase and, in addition, record the coupon they bought on their card," says the spokesperson for the Martin Optrný project.
Besides libraries, it will also be possible to record electronic coupons on the Opencard in automatic distributors installed in the vestibule of several metro stations.
What do these distributors look like?
They are red, remind the machines to compose the tickets and the passengers may have already noticed them in the metro stations Roztyly, Budějovická, I. P. Pavlova, Florenc and Vltavská.
"Today, the city has five, but by the end of the year, there should be ninety," Opatrný added.
An auto will control the coupon instead of the driver
The machines that will work from tomorrow are easy to use.
Just insert the Opencard chip card and the coupon previously purchased will register itself on the card.
Electronic coupons are valid from tomorrow not only in the capital, but also around the city.
