Issues that arise after the accident: The stewards in why are they illegal?
The law ignores them; walking in a long distance is forbidden
In the context of the tragic accident of the Student Agency bus company near Padua, Italy, the question arises whether stewards and passengers can travel within the coach.
"If the law was to be adhered to in a strict and formal manner, the activity of a steward is contrary to the Road Traffic Act," says Karel Hanzelka's spokesman.
The accident in question, during which a 22-year-old hostess died, was apparently caused by the driver of a truck that crossed the road to the bus.
The girl was at this time unfortunately sitting next to the driver, on the most dangerous seat of the vehicle, although she has two other seats at her disposal.
However, the coach can have an accident, or even slow down abruptly, even when the steward serves the coffee or distributes the newspapers.
What matters is whether the coach is on the basis of its technical data sheet equipped with standing seats or not.
If this standing equipment is not approved, passengers must remain seated.
The long distance buses Student Agency do not have standing seats; this was confirmed in Aktuálně.cz by the director of the company Radim Jančura.
"This is an issue that we have addressed with the ministry and, at first, it prohibits any travel of passengers.
Then they canceled it and we got that the passengers could go to the toilet during the journey provided they had their own seat," he unveiled.
The law ignores steward
"There is no single legal interpretation of the steward's role - there is no legal requirement for that role.
On the other hand, no legal requirements also prohibit the carrier from offering services.
The Road Transport Act only knows the term of the vehicle recipient; it does not define its rights and duties," adds the spokesman Hanzelka with more ambiguity.
Josef Pokorný, the director of the road traffic department, believes, on the contrary, that the law deals with the problem sufficiently.
"Everything depends on whether the coach has in its approval the permission to offer standing seats.
Everything is in there," he says.
Buses are divided into urban areas, where there are standing seats and a maximum speed of limited, interurban with standing seats and a higher permitted speed and in long distance buses without standing position with the highest authorized speed and seats equipped with safety-belts.
As in the plane, says an expert
Jaroslav Hořín, expert at BESIP (Security of Road Traffic) in Transport, does not see the movement of stewards on board as a major problem.
"The situation can be compared to that of the service in the aircraft.
Nor is it certain when a turbulence will occur and the air hostess can form her head."
"Now, in the event that the coach had stopped abruptly, the laws of physics would of course be valid.
In the same way as in an urban bus or tram.
The carrier must manage the security of stewards through internal requirements," he said, and he also felt that from the law's point of view, the problem was not resolved.
Jančura is ready to remove these services
Student Agency is the only bus carrier to offer the services of stewards.
He hires two hundred.
Even after this accident, the director does not regard his profession as a risky profession.
"None, as soon as I get the impression that this is a risky trade, I will delete it.
Passengers can receive their coffee and newspaper at boarding.
It would also reduce costs," he said.
The concern for safety is the reason why the director of Asiana Alexeï Litvine, who, in comparison with SA, provides a very small number of lines in his vehicles.
"We don't have hostesses, we've been opposing them since the beginning.
Sooner or later this will end in a fatal accident," he said, a year ago, at Týden.cz.
An immense tragedy has arrived.
A young hostess from the Plzeň region, who had been working for society for two years, died during the accident on the Naples line.
A Slovenian truck probably left the emergency stop band without using flashing and it blocked the way to the bus.
The driver tried to avoid it by means of a sudden maneuver, but he broke it on his right side.
Jančura refuses that the two seats reserved for the rest of the stewards were sold.
"In the case of long lines, it is not possible to reserve these places, they are blocked."
The company plans to file a complaint against the driver of the truck.
For the compensation of the girl's family, the agency will not wait for the court's judgment, but for the financial compensation, it also relies on the guilty party.
An amendment to the law?
Not in sight
An amendment of the Act, which has been being developed for more than a year by a group of thirty experts from the Ministry of Transport, could provide clarification on the movement of the stewards aboard the bus.
"Now, it has not come to any conclusion on this point.
In fact, she is not too interested in buses, but rather in the points system, at the maximum speed on the highway and in the use of the laptop by the wheel," said expert Hořín.
"The Ministry of Transport does not consider the activity of the stewards as something that would fundamentally endanger the safety of passengers," concludes Spokesman Hanzelka, pointing out that the control of the safety of buses is under the power of the police and the Office for Safety at Work.
The hopes of the Düsseldorfois are based on Frankfurt.
The big words were not missing in the letter from the WestLB Steering Committee to the employees of the house.
By a union of the entities of the financial institution of Düsseldorf with the Frankfurt Deka-Bank, "the central institution of the financial markets of the Sparkasse Financial Group" could be constituted, according to the letter published on Monday.
